  "original_title": "\u0dbb\u0db1\u0dca\u0da2\u0db1\u0dca \u0dc4\u0dd9\u0da7 \u0dc4\u0ddd \u0dc3\u0db3\u0dd4\u0daf\u0dcf \u0db1\u0dd2\u0daf\u0dc4\u0dc3\u0dca?",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Is Ranjan free tomorrow or Monday?",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Tourism and Lands Minister Harin Fernando says that he strongly believes that Mr. Ranjan Ramanayake will be freed either tomorrow or Monday.",
        "Mr. Harin Fernando, who posted a note on his Facebook account expressing his gratitude to the President for granting freedom to Mr. Ranjan Ramanayake, also mentions the following.",
        "\"My dear political colleague, I am very sure that Ranjan will be freed tomorrow (26) or Saturday (29). Thank you to Mr. Ranil Wickremesinghe, the President who fulfilled my and Manusha's request, and everyone who supported me, including Mr. Vjedasa Rajapaksa, the Minister of Justice, who performed a special mission!\" Mr. Harin Fernando has made a note."
      ],
